  "text": "To measure the cell surface density of ENaC, we used a hybrid construct of ␥-ENaC subunit and yellow fluorescent protein (YFP). To examine the functioning of Na ϩ conductance by ENaC, we assayed rapid Na ϩ -dependent self-inhibition of ENaC [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] . Our results show that the two parameters examined together account for most if not all of the reduction in ENaC conductance as a result of conserved residue mutations to alanine. Thus the charged residues examined appear to be functionally important mainly for structural configuration that affects Na ϩ self-inhibition and/or transport to the cell surface.",
